{
  "texts": [
    "Limitations and Future WorkIn our research, we measured the execution time of our programs under study in the CD case study and the 6-DOF case study.",
    "Execution time was included as a fitness function in our GA algorithm and in calculating the reward function in our RL algorithm.",
    "However, there were threats to the validity of our measured execution time.First threat was the factors that cause variation in the execution time of a program under test on a server are referred to as performance variability factors, which include:• Cache hits and misses.",
    "Data retrieval from cache or memory.• Other running programs.",
    "Resource consumption by other processes.• System load."
  ]
}